{
  "texts": [
    "Secondly, in-processing methods modify the machine learning algorithm during the training process to ensure fairness.",
    "These methods involve modifying the objective function or adding constraints to the optimization problem to ensure a fair outcome from the model.",
    "Examples of in-processing methods include adversarial training, where a separate model predicts the protected attribute and the original model ensures that it does not use this information to make predictions, and equalized odds, where the algorithm is optimized to ensure that the true-positive rates and false-positive rates are equal across different protected groups.",
    "Lastly, the post-processing methods involve modifying the output of the machine learning algorithm to ensure fairness.",
    "These methods involve adding a fairness constraint to the output, adjusting the decision threshold, or applying a re-weighting scheme to the predictions to ensure they are fair."
  ]
}